Geranium molle is a species of flowering plant in the family Geraniaceae. 
It is a small, herbaceous annual plant that can reach up to 30 cm in height. 
The leaves of Geranium molle are deeply cut and have five lobes. 
The flowers are small and have five petals that are pink to pale purple in color. 
Geranium molle can be found in a variety of habitats, including fields, pastures, and gardens. 
It is often used as a ground cover in landscaping. 
The plant is also known for its medicinal properties and has been used to treat a variety of ailments.
